#Text=The Milwaukee Bucks ( 13 - 21 ) defeated the Indiana Pacers ( 18 - 14 ) 120 - 116 on Thursday .
#Text=The New Year 's Eve showdown between the two Central Division rivals was atypical in a number of ways .
#Text=To begin with , one of the rarest sights in the NBA this season , a Bucks road victory , came to pass , and against a quality opponent to boot .
#Text=The Pacers had entered Thursday 's contest sporting an impressive 11 - 5 home record and playing quality basketball overall .
#Text=Meanwhile , Milwaukee had managed a paltry three wins in 18 tries away from the Bradley Center , including consecutive road losses to the Mavericks and Thunder preceding Thursday 's game .
#Text=They 'd also struggled offensively the majority of the year , often failing to even reach 100 points over the first 30 games of the season .
#Text=However , the light has seemingly come on for Milwaukee , and their side of the scoreboard , over their last two outings .

#Text=After tallying 123 points in the loss to Oklahoma City on Wednesday , the Bucks roared right back with another outstanding night on offense , shooting a stellar 58 percent from the field and 43 percent from beyond the arc .
#Text=They also managed 35 of their points off 20 Indiana turnovers .

#Text=As it turned out , they needed every one of those buckets before all was said and done , with the Pacers coming on strong with a 39 - point fourth quarter to make things close until the final seconds .
#Text=Milwaukee was once again led by standout guard Khris Middleton , who is in the midst of one of the hottest shooting stretches of his four - year career .
#Text=The Texas A & M product has now shot 63 percent from the field over his last two games , and collected 69 points in the process .

#Text=Thursday , Middleton managed 33 points , five rebounds , four assists , a block and a pair of steals to lead all scorers , including an impressive 4 - for - 6 performance from three - point range .
#Text=Greg Monroe pitched in with 23 points and three rebounds of his own , while Jabari Parker and Giannis Antetokounmpo contributed a pair of 14 - point efforts .
#Text=The former added three rebounds and an assist , while the latter had an outstanding defensive game as well , contributing six rebounds , four blocks and three steals .

#Text=Michael Carter-Williams closed out a remarkable night for the starters with a stat - sheet - stuffing 11 - point , seven - rebound , eight - assist effort that also included three steals and three blocks .
#Text=Jerryd Bayless paced the Bucks ' reserves with 14 points as well .
#Text=The Bucks improved to 13 - 21 but remain in last place in the Eastern Conference 's Central Division .
#Text=They now head to Minnesota for a Saturday showdown versus the Timberwolves .

#Text=Indiana 's starting five enjoyed a highly productive night , and were encouragingly led by a resurgent effort from All-Star Paul George , who 'd been struggling considerably with his shot in recent games .
#Text=The small forward exploded for 31 points on the strength of 8 of 13 shooting from the field , including a 5 - for - 9 performance from long distance .
#Text=After having shot an abysmal 28 percent ( 23 - for - 83 ) over the previous five contests , Thursday 's result was a particularly welcome sight for George and the Pacers .
#Text=C.J .
#Text=Miles shook off an ailing back to support George 's effort with 19 points , five rebounds , an assist and a steal .
#Text=George Hill followed with a 15 - point , six - rebound , three - assist night that also included a block .

#Text=Lavoy Allen continued to thrive in his starting opportunities in place of the ailing Ian Mahinmi , collecting 14 points and supplementing the scoring with four rebounds , three assists , a steal and a block .
#Text=Monta Ellis poured in 13 points and dished out seven assists , while Rodney Stuckey and Myles Turner led the reserves with a pair of eight - point efforts .
#Text=The Pacers fell to 18 - 14 and currently reside in third place in the Eastern Conference 's Central Division .
#Text=They remain home to face the Detroit Pistons on Saturday .
